    dc:creator "Huang, Chao; Mao, Si Ying; Huang, Jian Rong" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Two new potamid crabs, Yuexipotamon arcophallus new genus, new species and Minutomon shanweiense new genus, new species, (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Potamidae) from southern China" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231170>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231171>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231173>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231169> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231170>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Yuexipotamon arcophallus, new genus, new species, male holotype (21.7 × 18.1 mm) (SYSU 001005). A, dorsal overall view; B, frontal view of carapace; C, ventral view showing anterior thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, ventral view showing sterno-abdominal cavity with right G 1 in situ (left G 1 removed)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231170/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231171>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Yuexipotamon arcophallus, new genus, new species, male holotype (21.7 × 18.1 mm) (SYSU 001005). A, left G 2; B, left G 1 (ventral view); C, G 1 terminal segment (ventral view); D, left third maxilliped. (white bar = 1.0 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231171/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231173>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Yuexipotamon arcophallus, new genus, new species. Intraspecific variation. Left G 1 s (ventral views). A, holotype male (21.7 × 18.1 mm) (SYSU 001005); B, paratype male (21.6 × 18.1 mm) (SYSU 001008); C, paratype male (18.6 × 15.1 mm) (SYSU 001009); D, paratype male (19.6 × 17.2 mm) (SYSU 001007)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231173/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231169>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Yuexipotamon arcophallus, new genus, new species, colour in life. A, male holotype (21.7 × 18.1 mm) (SYSU 001005); B, typical burrow, arrows point at the two entrances." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231169/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

